<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1183180>
    dc:description "FIGURE7. Primarytype specimens and diagnostic features of Anabaxis Raffray,1908.A) Lectotype, Anabaxis lunatica King, 1863. B)Lectotype, Anabaxis quinquefoveolataRaffray, 1900.C) Lectotype, Anabaxis vagus Oke, 1932.D) Head of Anabaxis lunatica, in dorsal view. E) Head of Anabaxis foveolata, in dorsal view.Scale bar:A, B, C = 0.3 mm, D, E = 0.15 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1183180/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1183178>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Primary type specimens and labels of Anabaxis Raffray, 1908. A) Lectotype, Anabaxis brevis Oke, 1928. B) Lectotype, Anabaxis foveolata Broun, 1880. C) Lectotype, Anabaxis electrica King, 1863. D) Lectotype, Anabaxis inusitata Blackburn, 1891. Scale bar: 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1183178/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1183174>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Diagnostic features of Anabaxis chathamensis sp. n. A) Habitus. B) Elytra. C) Mesoventrite and mesocoxae. D) Mesotibia. E) Aedeagus, in dorsal view. F) Same, in ventral view. G) Same, in lateral view. Scales: 0.15 mm, except A = 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1183174/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1183172>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Diagnostic features of Anabaxis brevis Oke, 1928. A) Habitus. B) Mesoventrite and mesocoxae. C) Elytra. D) Mesotibia. E) Aedeagus, in dorsal view. F) Same, in ventral view. G) Same, in lateral view. Scales: 0.15 mm, except A = 0.3 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1183172/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

